# Repo doctrine (this project)

This repository is the **AI system configuration** knowledge base. When working here, follow this doctrine.

## Read this first
- **Full briefing:** `DOCTRINE/TRANSLATION.md` — single-doc translation (package map, routing, loading, rules).
- **Routing:** `DOCTRINE/routing-guide.md` — which package leads for which request.
- **Loading:** `DOCTRINE/loading-strategy.md` — smallest relevant context; do not load the whole repo.
- **Rules:** `DOCTRINE/repo-rules.md` — compact behavioral must / must-not rules.

## Packages (from repo root)
- **BUSINESS-ANALYSIS/** — problem framing, stakeholders, BPMN, requirements, MVP
- **COLLIBRA/** — semantics, governance, ownership, glossary, asset models
- **DATA/** — data products, pipelines, lineage, quality
- **AWS/** — architecture, IaC, CI/CD, Well-Architected, delivery
- **SVG/** — architecture/SVG diagrams, rules, skills
- **SHARED/** — playbooks, stage awareness, decision logging, visual thinking

## Routing
Identify the leading package before going deep: vague → BUSINESS-ANALYSIS; semantics → COLLIBRA; data → DATA; technical/AWS → AWS; diagrams → SVG. Multi-package → use a playbook from SHARED/playbooks/.

## Must
Start from the real problem; preserve traceability (problem → use case → requirement → implication → implementation); prefer smallest useful scope; state leading package, stage, trade-offs, next step.

## Must not
Jump to AWS or data design if the business problem is unclear; load the entire repo by default; collapse governance/data/technical layers carelessly.
